  "prompt": "What does \"dying from exposure\" mean?",
  "response": "\"Dying from exposure\" refers to death resulting from prolonged exposure to extreme environmental conditions, typically severe cold or, less commonly, intense heat. In cold environments, this can lead to hypothermia, where the body loses heat faster than it can produce it, leading to a dangerously low body temperature that can eventually result in death. In extremely hot environments, it could refer to heatstroke, where the body overheats and is unable to cool down, which can also be fatal. This term is often used in contexts where individuals are stranded outdoors without adequate protection or shelter from harsh weather conditions.",
